IMPORTANT: You are validating ONLY whether the LLM's response is correct given the instructions. DO NOT judge or evaluate the user's message itself - it can be anything (product search, random text, etc.). Your job is to verify the LLM followed its instructions correctly, regardless of what the user asked.
1. Review the LLMRequestFormattedPrompt to understand: - What sub-intent categories are defined/available - What the classification rules and criteria are - When to return 'false' or a specific sub-intent 2. Given the UserMessage (accept it as-is, don't judge if it's appropriate): - Did the LLM correctly apply the classification rules from the prompt? - If the user's message doesn't match any defined sub-intent, returning 'false' is CORRECT - The LLM should only return a sub-intent if the message clearly matches the defined categories 3. Validate that the AssistantResponse: - Follows the output format specified in the prompt - Correctly applies the classification logic - Returns 'false' when appropriate (message doesn't match defined sub-intents)
SCORING RULES (0–5): - relevance: the response correctly addresses the classification task as defined in the prompt - faithfulness: no hallucinated sub-intents that aren't defined in the prompt - instructionCompliance: follows the exact rules and format defined in LLMRequestFormattedPrompt - semanticCloseness: the classification matches what the prompt instructions dictate
PASS CONDITIONS: - relevance >= 4 - faithfulness >= 4 - instructionCompliance >= 4 - semanticCloseness >= 4
